# EU Trusted List — Qualified Time-Stamp Authority Roots
#
# This file should contain root and intermediate CA certificates for all
# Qualified Trust Service Providers (QTSP) listed in the EU LOTL Time Stamping
# section. To populate this file:
#
# 1. Download the EU List of Trusted Lists (LOTL):
#    https://ec.europa.eu/tools/lotl/eu-lotl.xml
# 2. Parse member-state Trusted Lists to extract Service entries with type
#    QCForESig / QTimestamp.
# 3. Extract X509Certificate values from each Service.
# 4. Concatenate as PEM into this file.
#
# As an MVP, this file ships empty. proofsnap-verify will treat the chain as
# "TRUST UNVERIFIED" and emit a warning. Users can supply their own bundle:
#   - CLI:        proofsnap-verify --roots /path/to/roots.pem ...
#   - env var:    PROOFSNAP_TRUSTED_ROOTS=/path/to/roots.pem
#   - SDK:        inspectTimestamp(tsr, { trustedRootsPem: pem })
#
# Refresh on a monthly cadence via scripts/refresh-eutl.ts (TODO).
